chunk_content: For an individual to be counted under this indicator, that individual’s HIV diagnosis must be confirmed using a nationally validated testing algorithm. For example, an HIV-positive rapid HIV test performed at the community- or facility- level must be confirmed following the national testing algorithm. If the confirmatory test is performed at a different site, then this requires follow-up by the reporting implementing partner to confirm the diagnosis before reporting under this indicator. The implementing partner who first identified and tested the individual should report on HTS_TST under the appropriate modality and age and sex disaggregate; however, that implementing partner must ensure that the diagnosis of the individual tested is confirmed. Only a confirmed diagnosis (positive or negative) counts under HTS_TST regardless of the modality used for reporting.
